645
01:04:13,345 --> 01:04:15,846
I know it's open-ended, but on the other hand,

646
01:04:17,447 --> 01:04:25,794
It adds other things that we're supposed to be handling, which historically, actually, we found out that it's very difficult to handle.

647
01:04:26,274 --> 01:04:30,438
And the open meeting law is not relevant to this discussion.

648
01:04:33,416 --> 01:04:35,237
all bound by the open readings law.

649
01:04:35,957 --> 01:04:55,924
And throughout the period that I've been involved, we are very careful, you know, to adhere to that law and to keep the discussions open to the public, obviously, and only discuss things openly when there's a quorum and so on and so forth.

650
01:04:56,524 --> 01:05:07,592
So again, I guess it's a matter of, I guess, opinion as to whether the ordinance should be updated or not.

651
01:05:07,772 --> 01:05:11,034
It hasn't been updated for many, many years.

652
01:05:11,835 --> 01:05:16,218
Again, I repeat myself by saying it asks us to do certain things that we don't actually do.

653
01:05:16,998 --> 01:05:31,027
For instance, the ordinance does not call for involvement, for instance, from the chief of police, which we historically have been always involved, you know, always thought it was useful.

654
01:05:31,808 --> 01:05:41,715
And, you know, Chief Buckley has become basically a permanent member of this commission, much the same as the previous chief of police.

655
01:05:42,455 --> 01:05:44,816
So that's the main idea.

656
01:05:44,936 --> 01:05:52,578
It's not the question of, does the Human Rights Commission have enough ideas to work with?

657
01:05:53,258 --> 01:05:54,319
That's not the point.

658
01:05:54,439 --> 01:06:10,484
The point is that the ordinance is outdated, and the hope is that we also bring in new ideas like, for instance, the possibility of maybe contacting the city and having

659
01:06:11,124 --> 01:06:19,247
reimbursement or some payments for members of the commission, especially for those members who have small children that need taking care of.

660
01:06:19,687 --> 01:06:23,609
So there are a lot of other ideas that are involved.

661
01:06:24,429 --> 01:06:33,313
Again, it's clearly the commission is as effective as the members who are working on it.

662
01:06:35,013 --> 01:06:39,775
And, you know, and your involvement in it is a good indication of that.

663
01:06:40,603 --> 01:06:51,359
But it doesn't mean necessarily that the current ordinance is, you know, very relevant to the work that the commission is doing.

664
01:06:53,841 --> 01:06:55,462
So I appreciate all of that.

665
01:06:55,642 --> 01:06:57,943
So thank you for sharing that.

666
01:06:58,083 --> 01:07:16,633
You know, I did, you know, in the last week, I did take another look at it and I believe, you know, one word like the mediate between the community, that might be something that you were highlighting about, you know, a role that you question us having.

667
01:07:16,673 --> 01:07:22,056
And as I thought about that, you know, and I work in the world of words as a writer and an editor,

668
01:07:23,743 --> 01:07:27,484
You know, immediate also means serves as an intermediary.

669
01:07:27,684 --> 01:07:37,106
So I had a moment where I thought, we can look at this in a broader sense where it's not just remediating conflict situations.

670
01:07:37,186 --> 01:07:46,228
We're also serving as an intermediary in the space of human rights between the city and the Medford community.

671
01:07:46,428 --> 01:07:50,209
And I thought, well, isn't that what I just did when I went to the,

672
01:07:51,047 --> 01:07:59,633
the Haitian flag raising event and shared that we have positions open I was an intermediary, on behalf of the commission in the city so I just.

673
01:08:02,002 --> 01:08:09,505
You know, and obviously if the city council is taking this up, you know, and I would hope they're doing it on behalf of all commissions.

674
01:08:09,565 --> 01:08:13,246
And I know that good work is being done on the charter study commission.

675
01:08:13,286 --> 01:08:28,972
Now there's a lot of antiquated language, but you know, I think that it's written broadly enough where we can see ourselves as intermediaries and I just don't want us to be disabled and going down a wrong, not a wrong path, just going down a path where

676
01:08:30,267 --> 01:08:43,136
We're not getting, you know, we're not taking action in the community and we just continue to be existential, you know, just reading and, you know, splitting hairs over some of the words.

677
01:08:43,216 --> 01:08:53,204
I think that I just like to step forward in action and I think it's written broadly enough so that we can, but I absolutely take everything you said seriously.

678
01:08:53,224 --> 01:08:56,486
And it'll be interesting to see what the city council comes up with.

679
01:08:56,506 --> 01:08:57,387
So thank you, Muneer.

680
01:09:00,065 --> 01:09:02,107
Matthew, I'm gonna give it to you.

681
01:09:02,147 --> 01:09:04,969
I've seen your hand go up and come down a few times.

682
01:09:06,891 --> 01:09:13,296
Yeah, I mean, I looked at this months ago and it was, you know, it was reassuring when Rob did the work and reported on April.

683
01:09:13,356 --> 01:09:24,885
That's something I was trying to communicate to City of Medford is that, I mean, there are just, there are a series of kind of self-contradicting claims about this ordinance.

684
01:09:25,146 --> 01:09:26,507
But when I looked at it,

685
01:09:27,047 --> 01:09:29,208
A while back, I saw that as well.

686
01:09:29,228 --> 01:09:31,088
It can be interpreted expansively.

687
01:09:31,608 --> 01:09:38,330
Another thing that's been realized is that the commission doesn't play by the word of what's actually in the ordinance.

688
01:09:38,370 --> 01:09:39,891
The commission is just doing whatever.

689
01:09:40,451 --> 01:09:47,313
Commission is just doing what people are interested in, not looking at the ordinance for guidance.

690
01:09:47,613 --> 01:09:54,375
There's a group saying that the ordinance has to be changed so that the commissioners can do certain actions.

691
01:09:55,615 --> 01:09:59,358
it's not sustainable, these arguments about why it should be changed.

692
01:10:01,699 --> 01:10:07,384
I think that the most important thing is the priorities of people that are on the body and what do they want to do.

693
01:10:08,084 --> 01:10:17,431
If nobody's being penalized for not following the letter of the law, the ordinance, then I don't really see why, because then you have to change the ordinance, then you have to convince people to follow the new ordinance.

694
01:10:18,172 --> 01:10:20,935
It's just kind of not the culture that's been followed.

695
01:10:21,275 --> 01:10:24,598
Most important thing is building up capacity, people that really, really want to do the work.

696
01:10:25,019 --> 01:10:35,429
And as far as the open meeting law, I know that has been claimed previously months ago by a chair that the chair of this body, that the open meeting law is kind of preventing the body, this body from doing work.

697
01:10:35,509 --> 01:10:38,172
It may have been like in November, December, something like this.

698
01:10:40,886 --> 01:10:50,934
I think, you know, you can set up subcommittees, and as long as you put up the notices, what, 48, 72 hours ahead, I think this commission can do as much work as people feel committed to.

699
01:10:50,954 --> 01:10:55,658
I mean, open meeting law just says that, something like, you know, it's like 48 or 72 hours.

700
01:10:56,159 --> 01:11:05,567
There's nothing preventing this committee from forming subcommittees for all kinds of stuff to do more work.

701
01:11:05,607 --> 01:11:06,748
Judy, you have your hands raised.

702
01:11:08,309 --> 01:11:17,876
Can you hold on, Muneer, until all the commissioners are done so that then we can make sure we finish and then fully open it up to public participation?

703
01:11:18,096 --> 01:11:18,917
Oh, all right, yeah.

704
01:11:18,997 --> 01:11:23,140
I'm sorry, but I need to clarify something that Muneer said.

705
01:11:23,660 --> 01:11:24,501
Do I have the right?

706
01:11:26,102 --> 01:11:29,965
Yes, you can definitely do that during public participation.

707
